by Aikoland » Sun May 30, 2021 11:21 pm

New Horissnia wrote:Every single communist country predominantly having red and yellow on the flag

Is it really a cliché if it reflects real life though? The colour red has been associated with left-wing politics since the French Revolution and, while I don't believe there is any inherent association of the colour yellow and the political left (I mean I'm a socialist and I, at the very least, don't think of 'the left' when I see the colour yellow used in flags [or other political contexts], but I could be wrong here), I feel that the usage of the colour in the flag of the Soviet Union is what inspired the usage of the colour in later communist states.
